50|$|The {{back porch}} is {{the portion of}} each scan line between the end (rising edge) of the {{horizontal}} <b>sync</b> <b>pulse</b> {{and the start of}} active video. It is used to restore the black level (300 mV) reference in analog video. In signal processing terms, it compensates for the fall time and settling time following the <b>sync</b> <b>pulse.</b>|$|E
