50|$|The {{front porch}} {{is a brief}} (about 1.5 microsecond) period {{inserted}} {{between the end of}} each transmitted line of picture and {{the leading edge of the}} next line <b>sync</b> <b>pulse.</b> Its purpose was to allow voltage levels to stabilise in older televisions, preventing interference between picture lines. The front porch is the first component of the horizontal blanking interval which also contains the horizontal <b>sync</b> <b>pulse</b> and the back porch.|$|E
